Fixed the garbled-text issue in `coworker\scripts\coworker.ps1`.

I added `Read-TaskFileContent` to read task files via BOM detection, strict UTF-8, then local code-page fallback, and `Convert-TaskFileToUtf8` to rewrite the task file as UTF-8 before the rename/move workflow continues. That keeps Chinese task content readable for downstream Copilot processing.

I intentionally left the separate missing-file/move problem untouched, per the task note.

Validation: I ran a focused PowerShell check with a GBK/CP936 Chinese sample file and confirmed it round-trips correctly after conversion to UTF-8.


